00:15:08.708 --> 00:15:10.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[panting slows]

210
00:15:13.875 --> 00:15:16.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing heavily]

211
00:15:17.458 --> 00:15:18.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, God.

212
00:15:20.583 --> 00:15:25.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure there must have been a time
when I had nice dreams.

213
00:15:25.458 --> 00:15:29.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[sighs] Maybe when
I lived in palaces and mansions?

214
00:15:31.458 --> 00:15:33.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But maybe not.

215
00:15:34.417 --> 00:15:36.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That was all stress.

216
00:15:37.083 --> 00:15:38.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doing my little dance for coins,

217
00:15:39.042 --> 00:15:41.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
making sure I had enough for the next...

218
00:15:41.958 --> 00:15:44.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs] month, the next year.

219
00:15:47.583 --> 00:15:49.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never bloody easy, was it?

220
00:15:49.250 --> 00:15:50.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[snaps fingers]

221
00:15:52.250 --> 00:15:54.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then...

222
00:15:54.625 --> 00:15:56.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
there was you.

223
00:15:58.875 --> 00:16:00.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did I dream when you were here?

224
00:16:02.125 --> 00:16:03.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know.

225
00:16:04.625 --> 00:16:07.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was too focused on our daylight hours.

226
00:16:09.167 --> 00:16:11.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I never wanted to sleep in those days.

227
00:16:13.333 --> 00:16:15.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And now here I am again.

228
00:16:16.875 --> 00:16:19.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Never wanting to sleep.

229
00:16:21.042 --> 00:16:23.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not until I find you.

230
00:16:25.125 --> 00:16:29.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Not until I live
in the good dream again.

231
00:16:30.042 --> 00:16:31.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[pen scratching on paper]

232
00:16:31.917 --> 00:16:34.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not until you're back.

233
00:16:51.042 --> 00:16:53.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where is the one who can talk well?

234
00:16:53.750 --> 00:16:55.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The one with the eyes?

235
00:16:55.625 --> 00:16:57.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I made you in Genoa.

236
00:17:05.542 --> 00:17:07.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You mean... me?

237
00:17:08.792 --> 00:17:11.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do. Sit with me a moment.

238
00:17:15.708 --> 00:17:18.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you wish?

239
00:17:18.667 --> 00:17:20.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was curious.

240
00:17:20.875 --> 00:17:24.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The night is long and I've been given
much to think about of late.

241
00:17:24.875 --> 00:17:27.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
May I ask a question of you?

242
00:17:27.375 --> 00:17:28.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course.

243
00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:30.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you remember who you were?

244
00:17:30.750 --> 00:17:32.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Before you went to hell.

245
00:17:33.417 --> 00:17:34.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I...

246
00:17:35.792 --> 00:17:37.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>almost </i>do.

247
00:17:38.750 --> 00:17:39.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's like...

248
00:17:40.625 --> 00:17:44.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I remember how it was to dream,

249
00:17:44.500 --> 00:17:48.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and to remember moments of the dream,

250
00:17:48.792 --> 00:17:52.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but never the entire play.

251
00:17:53.625 --> 00:17:54.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you see?

252
00:17:54.958 --> 00:17:56.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I do.

253
00:17:56.792 --> 00:17:58.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you remember?

254
00:17:58.458 --> 00:18:01.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was a scholar.

255
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Isaac]
Really?

256
00:18:04.208 --> 00:18:05.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was.

257
00:18:06.042 --> 00:18:09.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In a place called Athens.

258
00:18:10.292 --> 00:18:12.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think it was a long time ago.

259
00:18:12.917 --> 00:18:14.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you study?

260
00:18:14.500 --> 00:18:17.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was a philosopher.

261
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:21.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And this was a thing
that sent you to Hell?

262
00:18:21.542 --> 00:18:24.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I lived as a man during a time

263
00:18:24.917 --> 00:18:28.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when the empire that ruled Athens

264
00:18:28.833 --> 00:18:33.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
changed its religion and laws.

265
00:18:33.833 --> 00:18:36.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I believed philosophy

266
00:18:36.542 --> 00:18:40.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to be the study of the systems
of the world

267
00:18:40.625 --> 00:18:43.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and our purpose in it.

268
00:18:44.375 --> 00:18:48.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And yet discussion
of the nature of the divine

269
00:18:48.542 --> 00:18:50.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
became a crime.

270
00:18:52.375 --> 00:18:54.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who declared this a crime?

271
00:18:55.458 --> 00:18:57.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Christians.

272
00:18:59.125 --> 00:19:02.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To be a philosopher

273
00:19:02.583 --> 00:19:04.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was a sin.

274
00:19:04.583 --> 00:19:08.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And one important Christian

275
00:19:08.542 --> 00:19:10.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was heard to say

276
00:19:10.708 --> 00:19:15.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
that the people should hunt down sinners

277
00:19:15.667 --> 00:19:19.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and drive them into salvation,

278
00:19:19.708 --> 00:19:24.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as a hunter drives its prey into traps.

279
00:19:25.792 --> 00:19:30.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To think about God
would surely not be a sin in God's eyes.

280
00:19:31.333 --> 00:19:33.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[FlysEyes]
Perhaps.

281
00:19:33.167 --> 00:19:36.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And yet... here I am.

282
00:19:37.125 --> 00:19:38.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Isaac]
And perhaps

283
00:19:38.583 --> 00:19:40.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you have not told me
all of your dream.

284
00:19:41.667 --> 00:19:46.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[FlysEyes]
I was betrayed, Forgemaster.

285
00:19:47.583 --> 00:19:49.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was hunted.

286
00:19:49.542 --> 00:19:52.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was tortured.

287
00:19:52.583 --> 00:19:57.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I lied for my life...

288
00:19:57.417 --> 00:19:59.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in a church,

289
00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:01.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before a judge.

290
00:20:02.750 --> 00:20:05.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I gave up others

291
00:20:05.417 --> 00:20:09.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so that I may live.

292
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:13.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I<i> became </i>a sinner.

293
00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:17.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And?

294
00:20:17.333 --> 00:20:21.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[FlysEyes]
And they killed me anyway.

295
00:20:23.167 --> 00:20:25.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I woke up in Hell...

296
00:20:25.917 --> 00:20:29.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
because this world is insane.

297
00:20:29.958 --> 00:20:31.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And...

298
00:20:31.667 --> 00:20:35.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I learned something about sin.

299
00:20:37.542 --> 00:20:39.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you learn?

300
00:20:42.042 --> 00:20:43.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I learned...

301
00:20:44.833 --> 00:20:46.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to like it.

302
00:20:47.208 --> 00:20:50.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yet here I am,

303
00:20:50.375 --> 00:20:54.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
back on the surface of the Earth...

304
00:20:55.000 --> 00:20:57.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
strong and free,

305
00:20:58.042 --> 00:21:02.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in a world where thinking

306
00:21:02.667 --> 00:21:04.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
is considered something

307
00:21:05.042 --> 00:21:09.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that should be
tortured and murdered.

308
00:21:12.792 --> 00:21:16.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you for my second life.

309
00:21:18.083 --> 00:21:21.250 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
